r</b>. <br/><br/>Last week in New York, more than $1.3 billion in art chang=
ed hands at Bonhams, Christie=E2=80=99s, Phillips, and Sotheby=E2=80=99s. M=
ore to the point, reference prices were set for hundreds of artists=E2=80=
=94figures the art market will use to guide private sales over the next six=
 months, until we do this all over again in May. <br/><br/>Before we get in=
to the nitty-gritty of the market data and auction anecdotes, my topline ta=
ke is that it=E2=80=99s now clear we bottomed out in May. Even though the N=
ovember sales are 5 percent lower in total volume, data from ARTDAI and <u>=
