:0;list-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li><i>Lower estimates=
 lead to higher prices</i>: Before the auctions last week, I told you that =
the new art market calculus revolves around lowering estimates in order to =
get higher prices. Remember, the art market has a psychology of mistrust, a=
nd it is often easier to pay more if you see that others are willing to for=
k over close to the same price. A perfect illustration of this phenomenon e=
merged during Christie=E2=80=99s various-owners sale of modern art. A small=
 <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2=
