          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 22px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Turning to works wi=
th the highest hammer ratio, a record price of $864,000 was set for <b>Gert=
rude Abercrombie</b>, on a <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbW=
FpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUYXktZ2JlcjE3SGt3aU1DN3FQTT0iLCJocmVmI=
joiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm9uaGFtcy5jb20vYXVjdGlvbi8yOTUyMS9sb3QvMUEvZ2VydHJ1ZGUt=
YWJlcmNyb21iaWUtMTkwOS0xOTc3LXNpbG8tYXQtYWxlZG8tMzYtMTQteC0yNC1pbi05Mi14LTY=
wOS1jbS1wYWludGVkLWluLTE5NTMvP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1XYWxsK1Bvd2VyKy0rU1VCU0NSSU=
JFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYyNiUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9V2FsbCtQb3dlcistK1NVQ=
lNDUklCRVJTKyUyODExJTJGMTclMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9u=
XHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmF=
iZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MTk5NDg0NX=
0/42b1f6b55b2e4252ce90eeb2505e3e0075e4a5965d1c702b95abc45f8965b310" style=
=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">work=
</a></u> estimated at a mere $100,000, at Bonhams. Abercrombie is one of a =
group of female surrealist painters whose work has become increasingly valu=
able in recent years. At Sotheby=E2=80=99s, three of her works, all quite s=
mall, were sold for huge prices, ranging from $192,000 to $264,000. The rem=
aining works on the list
of lots with the most dynamic bidding were all estimated at $20,000 or belo=
w. The art market continues to trawl through the day sales for historic wor=
ks that are perceived to be undervalued. This season, <b>John Ritchie,</b> =
<b>Emilio Baz Viaud</b>, <b>Raymond Barker</b>, <b>Herbert Bayer</b>, <b>Ju=
dith Rothschild</b>, <b>Alfredo Casta=C3=B1eda</b>, <b>Emmanuel Man=C3=A9-K=
atz</b>, and <b>John Opper</b> were all in the spotlight. <br/> <br/>The to=
p artists by market share were a familiar group in an unfamiliar order. Mag=
ritte was by far the most appealing artist, with more than 13 percent of th=
e dollars spent going to work by the Belgian surrealist. Ruscha was second,=
 with 7.5 percent. The former market leaders, <b>Claude Monet</b> and <b>Pa=
blo Picasso</b>, slid to third and fourth position. <b>Alberto Giacometti <=
/b>and <b>David Hockney</b> followed. <b>Roy Lichtenstein</b> posted a stro=
ng showing with nearly 3 percent of spending. Basquiat came in just behind =
him. <b>Joan
Mitchell</b>, <b>Fran=C3=A7ois-Xavier Lalanne</b>, <b>Willem de Kooning</b>=
, and <b>Wassily Kandinsky</b> rounded out the top 12. <br/></td>
